### Step 3: Connect Outputs to the 7-Segment Display

Remember the 7-segment display has 7 input pins that each control one LED segment. The 74LS48 IC both converts the 4-bit binary input into the decimal number to display, and outputs the correct light-up pattern of the 7 segments in its 7 output pins. This is why we call this IC a BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) to 7-Segment Decoder. We just need to connect the a-g output pins on the IC to the corresponding a-g input pins on the 7-segment display. Here is the pinout diagram again for reference. 

<figure class="figure">
  <img src="COURSE/modules/mod1/ex1/7segment-pinout.png">
  <figcaption>7-segment display pinout</figcaption>
</figure>

```
